ias1_presentation.text: Financial statements shall present fairly the financial position, financial performance and cash flows of an entity.
When applying IFRSs, an entity shall select and apply accounting policies consistently for similar transactions and events.
An entity shall disclose information that is relevant to an understanding of the financial statements, including significant accounting policies.

ias36_impairment.text: An entity shall assess at the end of each reporting period whether there is any indication that an asset may be impaired.
If there is an indication of impairment, the entity shall estimate the recoverable amount of the asset.
The recoverable amount is the higher of an asset's fair value less costs of disposal and its value in use.

ifrs16_leases.text: Lessee shall recognise a right-of-use asset and a lease liability at the commencement date of the lease.
The discount rate used shall be the interest rate implicit in the lease if readily determinable; otherwise, the lessee's incremental borrowing rate shall be used.
Right-of-use assets and lease liabilities shall be presented separately or disclosed in the notes.
